<li><a href="http://oasis.harvard.edu:10080/oasis/deliver/~env00007" class="external text" title="http://oasis.harvard.edu:10080/oasis/deliver/~env00007" rel="nofollow">Guide to Nuclear Winter Study Papers, 1972-1993.</a> <a href="/wiki/Lawrence_Livermore_Laboratory" title="Lawrence Livermore Laboratory" class="mw-redirect">Lawrence Livermore Laboratory</a></li>
<li>Robock, Alan, Luke Oman, Georgiy L. Stenchikov, Owen B. Toon, Charles Bardeen, and Richard P. Turco, 2007a: <a href="http://climate.envsci.rutgers.edu/pdf/acp-7-2003-2007.pdf" class="external text" title="http://climate.envsci.rutgers.edu/pdf/acp-7-2003-2007.pdf" rel="nofollow">Climatic consequences of regional nuclear conflicts.</a> <i>Atm. Chem. Phys.</i>, <b>7</b>, 2003-2012.</li>
<li>Robock, Alan, Luke Oman, and Georgiy L. Stenchikov, 2007b: <a href="http://climate.envsci.rutgers.edu/pdf/RobockNW2006JD008235.pdf" class="external text" title="http://climate.envsci.rutgers.edu/pdf/RobockNW2006JD008235.pdf" rel="nofollow">Nuclear winter revisited with a modern climate model and current nuclear arsenals: Still catastrophic consequences.</a> <i>J. Geophys. Res.</i>, <b>112</b>, D13107, <a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1029/2006JD008235" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1029/2006JD008235" rel="nofollow">doi:10.1029/2006JD008235</a>.</li>
